window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Wellman's work will be remembered, and should be preserved because it combines the dark gothic tradition of the American pulps with a detailed snapshot of regional history and culture. This mixture is shown through the lens of the American modernist tradition, revealing something that is larger than the sum of its parts. </p><p>This is Volume Two of a five-volume set collecting all of Wellman's Appalachian fantasy stories. Contents: </p><ul><li>\"The Devil Is Not Mocked\" </li> <li>\"The Pineys\" </li> <li>\"Hundred Years Gone\" </li> <li>\"Where the Woodbine Twineth\" </li> <li>\"Keep Me Away\" </li> <li>\"Come into My Parlor\" </li> <li>\"Yare\" </li> </ul><p>And more! </p>"; 
